            <div class="ag-label">Career</div>
            <h2>One of the most distinguished careers in modern drumming</h2>
            <p>Gordy Knudtson is a professional drummer, educator, and author whose career spans more than four decades at the highest levels of the music industry. He is best known as the drummer for the <strong>Steve Miller Band</strong>, a role he held for more than thirty years after joining the band in 1987.</p>
            <p>During his tenure with the Steve Miller Band, Gordy performed on recordings and tours that reached audiences around the world. In 2016, he was part of the band's induction into the <strong>Rock and Roll Hall of Fame</strong> — one of the most prestigious honors in popular music.</p>
            <p>Before and alongside his work with the Steve Miller Band, Gordy built a diverse career as a sideman and collaborator. He has worked with <strong>Booker T. &amp; the MGs</strong>, jazz pianist <strong>Ben Sidran</strong> (a six-year collaboration), guitarist <strong>Roy Buchanan</strong>, and Cuban pianist <strong>Nachito Herrera</strong>, among many others.</p>
            <p>Gordy began drumming at age fifteen and turned professional at seventeen — a trajectory that reflects both natural talent and a lifelong commitment to the instrument.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ag-gray">
