            <div class="ag-label">Education</div>
            <h2>A career in teaching as distinguished as his performing career</h2>
            <p>Gordy's commitment to drum education has been a defining thread throughout his career. He headed the <strong>Percussion Department at McNally Smith College of Music</strong> in St. Paul, Minnesota — one of the leading contemporary music schools in the United States.</p>
            <p>His work as an educator goes beyond classroom instruction. Gordy has made significant contributions to the broader drumming community through clinics, workshops, and published research into drumming technique.</p>
            <p>Most notably, he developed and published <strong>Open/Close Technique</strong> — a systematic approach to hand technique that was featured in <em>Percussive Notes Magazine</em> and presented at <strong>PASIC 2003</strong> alongside legendary drummers Joe Morello and Jim Chapin. The late <strong>Ed Shaughnessy</strong> described Open/Close Technique as <em>"an historically important form of technique that ranks with the Moeller system."</em></p>
        </div>
    </div>

